# Node.js Backend (NestJS)

## Structure

Organize by domain module (matches `specs/Architecture.md`):

```
apps/api/src/
├── auth/
├── admin/
├── director/
├── assignments/
├── submissions/
├── attendance/
├── parent-dashboard/
└── common/          guards, filters, decorators
```

Each module: `*.module.ts`, `*.controller.ts`, `*.service.ts`, `dto/`, `entities/`.

## Conventions

- Use **class-validator** + **class-transformer** on DTOs; mirror `specs/Openapi.yml` schemas
- Controllers: thin — delegate to services; return types match OpenAPI
- Services: business rules from Gherkin scenarios in `specs/Userstories.md`
- Inject repositories; no raw SQL in controllers

## Auth & RBAC

```typescript
// ✅ Guard per route
@Roles('teacher', 'admin')
@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard, RolesGuard)

// ✅ Scope queries by tenant + ownership
async findStudentAssignments(studentId: string, user: AuthUser) {
  await this.guardianGuard.assertCanAccessStudent(user, studentId);
  return this.repo.findByStudent(studentId, user.schoolId);
}
```

- JWT payload: `sub`, `role`, `school_id`, optional `student_id`
- Never trust client `school_id`; read from token

## API errors

```typescript
// ✅ Consistent shape (matches Openapi.yml ErrorResponse)
throw new BadRequestException({
  error: { code: 'VALIDATION_ERROR', message: '...', details: [] },
});
```

## Database

- PostgreSQL via TypeORM or Prisma — schema follows `specs/Database.md`
- Migrations required for every schema change
- Use transactions for multi-table writes (e.g. submission + notification event)

## Events & notifications

- Publish domain events async (BullMQ): `AttendanceRecorded`, `AssignmentGraded`
- FCM push in worker, not in request handler

## Testing

- Unit: services + guards
- Integration: Supertest per endpoint; cover 200, 401, 403, 400
- Reference `specs/Testing.md` for story → test mapping

## Do not

- Put secrets in code; use env vars
- Expose `password_hash`, internal IDs cross-tenant
- Skip OpenAPI update when adding endpoints
- Duplicate business rules in controllers or frontend (DRY → service layer)
- Add abstractions for single-use cases (KISS/YAGNI)
- Use empty catch blocks or generic `throw new Error()` (clean code)
